The country is losing vital professionals according to the South African Institution of Civil Engineering. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African Institution of Civil Engineering is concerned the country is losing valuable skills in the form of engineers leaving South Africa. Engineers are apparently leaving the country to use their skills abroad. READ: Public Works team to assess Sophiatown police flats SAICE wants the government to put measures in place that will attract them back to South Africa. Steven Kaplan, the acting CEO of SAICE, said there needs to be a much stronger engineering presence in the infrastructure departments of the government. READ: 'Construction mafia' disrupt major projects Kaplan said the government must deliver on the promises made about infrastructure development and stimulate the construction industry to retain local engineers and possibly entice those who have left to come back.